{"id":413921461,"lang":"python3","time":"8Â months","timestamp":1603838422,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"52 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/413921461/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Trapping Rain Water","memory":"14.8 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def trap(self, arr: List[int]) -> int:\n        # O(n) time and space | two pass\n        maxH = 0\n        n = len(arr)\n        dp = [0] * n\n        for i, h in enumerate(arr):\n            maxH = max(maxH, h)\n            dp[i] = maxH - h\n        maxH = 0\n        ans = 0\n        for i in range(n-1, -1, -1):\n            h = arr[i]\n            maxH = max(maxH, h)\n            ans += min(dp[i], maxH - h)\n        return ans","compare_result":"","title_slug":"trapping-rain-water"}
